#!/bin/bash
# dev-keys — quick-reference keybinding cheat sheet
# Same content as Space+? inside neovim

cat << 'EOF'
╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║                     DEV IDE MANUAL                          ║
╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
║                                                             ║
║  PANE NAVIGATION (tmux + neovim)                            ║
║    Ctrl+h/j/k/l      Move between panes                    ║
║    Ctrl+a d           Detach (reattach with: dev)           ║
║                                                             ║
║  TMUX (prefix = Ctrl+a)                                     ║
║    Ctrl+a |           Vertical split                        ║
║    Ctrl+a -           Horizontal split                      ║
║    Ctrl+a c           New window                            ║
║    Ctrl+a n / p       Next / prev window                    ║
║    Ctrl+a z           Toggle pane fullscreen                ║
║    Ctrl+a H/J/K/L     Resize pane                           ║
║    Ctrl+a [           Copy mode (vi keys, q to exit)        ║
║                                                             ║
║  FILE TREE (Space e toggles, tree on the right)             ║
║    Enter              Open file                             ║
║    a                  Create file (add / for folder)        ║
║    d                  Delete                                ║
║    r                  Rename                                ║
║    c / x / p          Copy / cut / paste                    ║
║    m                  Move                                  ║
║    H                  Toggle hidden files                   ║
║    /                  Filter / search                       ║
║                                                             ║
║  FIND (fuzzy search)                                        ║
║    Space ff           Find files by name                    ║
║    Space fg           Search file contents (grep)           ║
║    Space fb           Switch between open buffers           ║
║                                                             ║
║  GIT                                                        ║
║    Space gg           Open lazygit (full git TUI)           ║
║    Space gs           Git status (modified files list)      ║
║    Space gc           Git commit log                        ║
║    Space gb           Git branches                          ║
║    Space hb           Toggle git blame on current line      ║
║    Space hp           Preview hunk diff                     ║
║    Space hs / hu      Stage / undo stage hunk               ║
║    Space hr           Reset hunk (discard change)           ║
║    Space hd           Diff current file                     ║
║    ] h / [ h          Jump to next / prev changed hunk      ║
║                                                             ║
║  CODE (LSP)                                                 ║
║    gd                 Go to definition                      ║
║    gr                 Find references                       ║
║    K                  Hover docs                            ║
║    Space ca           Code action (quick fix)               ║
║    Space rn           Rename symbol                         ║
║                                                             ║
║  EDITING                                                    ║
║    i                  Enter insert mode (start typing)      ║
║    Esc                Back to normal mode                   ║
║    :w                 Save  |  :q  Quit  |  :wq  Both      ║
║    u / Ctrl+r         Undo / redo                           ║
║    V then J/K         Move selected lines up/down           ║
║    Ctrl+d / Ctrl+u    Scroll half-page (centered)           ║
║    Space              Press and wait — shows all keybinds   ║
║                                                             ║
║  QUICK START                                                ║
║    1. Space e         Open file tree                        ║
║    2. Navigate + Enter to open a file                       ║
║    3. i to edit, Esc then :w to save                        ║
║    4. Space gg        Review changes in lazygit             ║
║    5. Ctrl+h          Jump to Claude pane                   ║
║    6. Ctrl+l          Jump back to editor                   ║
║                                                             ║
║  In neovim: Space+? opens this same manual                  ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
EOF
